Adventure 1 Companion: Windhelm City Profile & Reference
Main Document: Adventure 1: First Steps — The Windhelm Catacombs — runs the session. Contains all scenes, read-alouds, dungeon sections, dialogue, clues, all combat stat blocks inline where they're used, and the Ismara background activity.
This document is for prep and between-scene reference. It contains the Windhelm city profile, city events table, persistent NPC profiles with stat blocks for non-combat NPCs, and contingencies (Calixto variant, Hook redirect). You do not need to open this document during combat or mid-scene.

Windhelm — City Profile 
Pillar 1: Structure
Name & High Concept: Windhelm — The oldest city in Skyrim, seat of Ulfric Stormcloak's political movement, built on Atmoran foundations over a segregated underclass.
Size & Scale: City. Multiple inns and shops, distinct districts (Stone Quarter, Gray Quarter, Docks), Palace of the Kings, multiple unique locations.
Atmosphere & Core Conflict: Ancient, cold, proud, and fractured. The Nords live in the Stone Quarter with its dark stone buildings and ancestral wealth. The Dunmer live in the Gray Quarter — a ghetto in everything but name. The Argonians work the docks and are barred from the city proper. Ulfric's political project consumes all available attention and resources, leaving the city's internal problems to fester.
Regional Favor: Windhelm values Nord tradition, loyalty to the Stormcloak cause, and martial prowess. Favor is gained by showing combat skill, respecting Nord customs, and ancestor worship. Disdain is earned by supporting the Empire, showing sympathy to non-Nords (especially Elves), or relying on magic.
