Pillar 2: Inhabitants
Persistent NPC 1: Brunwulf Free-Winter
Name & Role: Brunwulf Free-Winter, retired veteran and advocate for Windhelm's non-Nord population.
Core Motivation: To see Windhelm treat its Dunmer and Argonian residents with basic dignity. He has been fighting this fight for years and is losing.
Current State (Initial): Present at Candlehearth Hall most evenings. Buys rounds for strangers. Asks polite questions. He's the only Nord in the city who regularly visits the Gray Quarter and the docks.
Potential Evolution:
Positive: If the party helps the Gray Quarter or the docks in any way, Brunwulf becomes a reliable ally and information source. He knows Windhelm's underside better than anyone in the Stone Quarter.
Negative: If the party supports the quarantine of the Gray Quarter or ignores Dunmer suffering, Brunwulf withdraws. He's tired. He doesn't have the energy for people who make things worse.
Quest: Brunwulf asks the party to check on a Dunmer family near the docks whose father hasn't come home in three days. This leads to one of Calixto's victims — a thread into the main investigation.
Persistent NPC 2: Viola Giordano
Name & Role: Viola Giordano, nosy busybody and self-appointed neighborhood watch.
Core Motivation: To be important. To be seen as someone who matters in a city that has bigger problems than her.
Current State (Initial): The party rescues her from Calixto's workshop. She is terrified, grateful, and will immediately begin telling everyone in Windhelm what happened. Her version of events will be loud, somewhat inaccurate, and will make the party famous.
Potential Evolution:
Positive: Viola becomes the party's most enthusiastic (and least accurate) advocate. She tells everyone about the brave heroes who saved her from the catacomb necromancer. This contributes to their reputation but also attracts attention they might not want.
Negative: If the party is dismissive of her, she tells a version of events where she saved herself and the party was incidental. Petty but harmless.
Persistent NPC 3: Suvaris Atheron
Name & Role: Suvaris Atheron, Dunmer beggar in the Gray Quarter. Cannibal.
Core Motivation: She cannot articulate what she wants. She is drawn to consume the dead. She does not understand why. She is ashamed. She is also unable to stop.
Current State (Initial): Sitting in an alley off the Gray Quarter's main street, eating from a cloth bundle she hides when approached.
Potential Evolution:
Positive (Orc engages): If the Orc approaches without judgment and engages with what Suvaris is experiencing, the Namira thread begins. Suvaris becomes a recurring figure — present in the Gray Quarter, increasingly drawn to the frozen people as they appear, a mirror for whatever the Orc is becoming.
Negative: If confronted with disgust or reported to authorities, Suvaris disappears. She is not seen again. The Namira thread goes quiet but does not end — it simply moves underground.
Neutral: If no one engages, she remains. A strange detail in a strange city.

Pillar 3: Events
Roll on this table if the party spends a full day in Windhelm doing downtime, or when they enter a new area of the city and you want texture.
d10
Event
1
Guard Shakedown: Stormcloak sympathizers are harassing a Dunmer merchant in the Stone Quarter market. Guards are watching but not intervening. Intervention earns Gray Quarter trust, potential Nord disdain.
2
Ulfric's Recruiter: A charismatic Stormcloak officer is giving a speech in the market square about the Empire's betrayal. He's good. The crowd is listening. If the party watches, he notices them afterward and approaches.
3
Khajiit Caravan Arrival: Ri'saad's caravan is setting up outside the gates. They have rare alchemical ingredients and one minor enchanted item. They also have information about the roads — frozen people standing in the Pale.
4
Temple Gathering: A service at the Temple of Arkay draws a crowd. Helgrid is conducting a blessing for the sick. If the party attends, they see how many people in Windhelm are quietly unwell — not Pale Fever, just the ordinary sickness of a city that's been neglecting its population.
5
Dock Incident: An Argonian worker has collapsed at the docks. The guards say it's exhaustion. The Argonians say something else. If the party investigates: rotgut skooma, sold by a Nord who doesn't care what it does to the workers. Side content, not plot.
6
Gray Quarter Tension: A group of Nord youths is throwing stones at a Dunmer's window. Brunwulf is walking toward them but hasn't arrived yet. The party can intervene before he does or let him handle it.
7
Wulfgar Sighting: The party sees an elderly man carrying an armload of stone tablets from the Palace toward the Hall of the Dead. If they help him, he's grateful and chatty. This is Wulfgar, going to compare tablets with the catacomb inscriptions. He'll share his work with anyone who shows interest.
8
Calixto's Tour: If the party hasn't met Calixto yet, they see a small group leaving his House of Curiosities, laughing and impressed. A sign outside reads "Tours Daily — See the Wonders of Tamriel's Past." He spots them and waves enthusiastically.
9
Sudden Snow: A heavy snowfall hits the city, forcing everyone indoors for a few hours. Candlehearth is packed. Perfect opportunity for conversation with NPCs who might not otherwise be in the same room.
10
Quiet Day: Nothing unusual. The city goes about its business. Use this for Order of Business scenes and personal arcs.


