Calixto's Motivation — GM Only:
Do not define who "her" is before the session. Calixto says "to bring her back" in the boss fight. If the party presses for details — in combat or if they somehow talk him down — he will say only: "She was — she understood what I was trying to do. She believed in it. And then she was gone." He does not name her. He does not explain the relationship. This is deliberate ambiguity — a lover, a mentor, a collaborator, a daughter. Whatever lands hardest for your table in the moment is correct. Decide in the moment, not in advance.

