Calixto Variant: Party Never Met Him Above Ground
If the party goes straight to the catacombs without ever visiting Candlehearth Hall or the House of Curiosities, they will encounter Calixto in Section 4 without knowing who he is.
Replace the boss fight read-aloud with:
"The fissure drops you into the largest chamber yet. Ceiling arching twenty feet above, pillars carved as warriors, iron braziers at each corner.
A man stands at the far end, hunched over a crude altar of bones. He's wearing fine clothes — ruined now, stained with blood and alchemical residue. Not armor. Not robes. The clothes of someone who belongs in a drawing room, not a crypt. His hands shake as he carves notation into the skin of a bound man on the altar.
Behind him, something massive looms by the cracked sarcophagus. Nine feet tall, ancient plate armor, a greatsword of black iron. Its eyes are on the man's back.
He hears you. He turns. His eyes are fevered."
The dialogue is the same. The difference is the party doesn't have the "wait — that's the friendly museum guy" moment. Instead they have a "who is this person and why is he here" moment. Both work. The version where they met him first is better.
After the fight, if the party searches his body or his workshop, they find the House of Curiosities key. If they visit the House afterward, they find a legitimate (if eccentric) collection of antiquities, and they realize this man had a public life in the city that nobody connected to the disappearances. Viola can fill in this gap: "The museum man. He gave tours. Everyone liked him."

Hook Contingency: Party Doesn't Go to the Temple First
If the party goes to Candlehearth Hall, the Gray Quarter, or anywhere else before the temple, the Hook still fires — it just fires differently.
Option A: Hrolf finds them.
Hrolf knows where they're staying (he waved them through the gate). When the first victim arrives at the temple, Helgrid sends Hrolf to find the party. He bursts into Candlehearth or the Gray Quarter:
"The heroes — the Frostmere people — where are they? There's something at the temple. Helgrid sent me. She says you need to see this."
He leads them to the temple. Helgrid shows them the dockworker's marks. The Khajiit's examination happens here too — Helgrid examines both sets of marks together. The scene plays the same, just slightly reordered.
Option B: They hear about it.
If they're at Candlehearth, word reaches the inn within the hour. A guard comes in and mentions "some kind of sickness at the temple — marks on a man's skin, glowing." Calixto, if present, is immediately interested: "Glowing marks? That sounds Atmoran. We should look at this."
Either way, the party ends up at the temple seeing the marks. The Khajiit's rotjoint examination can happen at the same time or immediately after.

